videos.description: Tennessee's Jordan Bone saves the turnover after the Vanderbilt bucket and hits a pull up jumper at the other end.
videos.headline: Bone puts on the brakes to drop defender and hits jumper

videos.description: Aaron Nesmith makes the transition layup off the steal and gives Vanderbilt their first lead after being down by as much as 15 points.
videos.headline: Nesmith gives Vandy first lead of game

videos.description: Tennessee's Kyle Alexander gets back on defense and sends Simisola Shittu's shot into the stands.
videos.headline: Alexander gets another big block

videos.description: World Series champion Mookie Betts joins the broadcast and shows his support for Tennessee basketball.
videos.headline: Mookie Betts talks Tennessee basketball

videos.description: Tennessee's Jordan Bowden gets the dunk off the in-bounds pass from Jordan Bone.
videos.headline: Bowden gets monster dunk off in-bound pass

videos.description: C. Brown made Dunk. Assisted by S. Lee.
videos.headline: Clevon Brown made Dunk. Assisted by Saben Lee.

videos.description: Tennessee's Grant Williams and Vanderbilt's Aaron Nesmith have huge blocks for their teams, sending the game to overtime.
videos.headline: Blocks on both ends prevent go-ahead buckets

videos.description: Grant Williams drives in and completes the tough and-1 layup to give Tennessee the lead in overtime.
videos.headline: Williams powers through for and-1 bucket

videos.description: Vanderbilt's Matt Ryan misses the 3-pointer and Aaron Nesmith gets ejected for actions after the rebound.
videos.headline: Ryan misses 3-pointer to tie for Vandy

videos.description: Grant Williams was a perfect 23-23 from the free throw line as he drops 43 points to lead No. 1 Tennessee in a 88-83 overtime win over Vanderbilt.
